sentences: An Yu-jin (Korean: 안유진; born September 1, 2003), better known mononymously as Yujin, is a South Korean singer.

She is the leader of the South Korean girl group Ive under Starship Entertainment and a former member of the temporary South Korean-Japanese girl group Iz*One for 2.5 years following her finishing in fifth place in Mnet's girl group survival show Produce 48.
Off the Record revealed in 2019 that she had quit school to focus on her idol life and Iz*One activities and will be home-schooled.
